Kernel Build Automation Script

A Bash-based automation project to compile and package Android/Linux kernels using Clang/LLVM or GCC.
It automates cloning, configuration, compilation, and zip packaging via AnyKernel3, reducing manual build steps.

üß© Features

One-command kernel build (via clone.sh and run.sh)

Supports both Clang and GCC toolchains

Auto packaging using AnyKernel3

Build logs and optional zip signing

